Text.string: Your assistance is required, Vault Hunter.
These quakes will destroy us all.
No, no—you are missing the point, Sparrow. If the quakes do not stop, we could all perish!
Whatever! TRIANGLES!

I am picking up a radio frequency, meaning you have successfully placed the beacon, instead of being consumed by nightmare beasts. If Sparrow had half the survival skills you possess, we would have already tamed this inhospitable planet.
I've got survival skills. Watch!
You are currently on fire.
Oh, crap!||—Wait, no, I'm not! Haha, you got me.
I have noted an additional frequency, meaning instead of being torn asunder by voracious animals, you have placed the other beacon. Good. Now, I will triangulate. One moment.
Grouse, you're on FIRE! Look! Grouse! Hey!

Please, Sparrow. I'm trying to concentrate. Okay, sending you coordinates, Vault Hunter... interesting. The Nekroquakes are coming from a subterranean abscess, or “cave”, in common parlance. We will create an opening with the explosives. Called it.
Now, proceed underground and find the source of those quakes.
Surely you've felt the Nekroquakes, Vault Hunter. It must be Maliwan's doing.
Surely the Nekroquakes are Maliwan's doing. But their time will come. Then we will exterminate this planet's fauna one by one, and finally all will be quiet...
That sorta sounded like you want to kill every living thing on the planet but us.
Yes. It did sound like that, Sparrow. It did sound like that.
But, heh, you're not going to kill me, right?
Not if you fulfill your primary protocols.
Which are...
Keeping our living environment clean and orderly.
And if I forget to clean, like, one day?
That would be... unfortunate.
“Slap on the wrist” unfortunate, or “scrap me” unfortunate?
All right! Quake time, best time!
Dealer's choice. And I am the dealer.
Hmm, it wasn't Maliwan after all. That is what caused the quakes. Clearly, this is Sparrow's crippling incompetence at work.
Uh, what?
I will deal with him later. You still have those explosives, yes, Vault Hunter?
Cool!
No—you are missing the... I hate you. That should do it, Vault Hunter. Return to me for a token of my appreciation. But to set expectations it is not merely a token, but money.
Vault Hunter, ride the air stream! Catch it!
Do not do that.
Come on, it'll be fun!
It will not be “fun”.

As you can see, Sparrow finds the Nekroquakes “fun” and “cool”—but if they continue, this planet will be torn apart and everything will perish. Which is objectively “not cool”. You must use those beacons to discover the source of the quakes.
The Nekroquakes have stopped. Thank you, Vault Hunter. Our survival is assured. For now.
Take some explosives as well. Just in case.
To start, place the first beacon.
Good. Now, just two more. We must triangulate the beacons to determine the Nekroquake's source.
You can't create a triangle without three points. No, don't get out paper. I know triangles.
Triangles are rad!
